  "name": "Serves 4",
  "recipeIngredient": [
    "l kg firm medium ceps",
    "6 8 garlic cloves, peeled and sliced",
    "200g butter",
    "salt and freshly ground black pepper",
    "2 tbsp chopped parsley"
  ],
  "recipeInstructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 2 20\u00b7 C/gas mark 7. Clean the ceps with a cloth and make about 5 1nc1sions in each one with the point of a k111fe. Push a slice of garlic into each incision.",
    "Melt half of the butter in a roasting tray Add the ceps, turn to coat them 1n the butter and season generously with salt and pepper. Roast in the oven for 20 30 minutes until the ceps are just tender, turning them every so often to ensure they cook and colour evenly.",
    "Add the rest of the butter and the chopped parsley, stir well and return to the oven for 2 3 minutes Serve at once."
  ],
